elements.textContent:
Introverts: Recharge by spending time alone; can feel drained by social interaction.
Extroverts: Recharge by spending time with others; can feel drained by solitude.
Introverts: Process information internally; may need time to reflect before responding.
Extroverts: Process information externally; often think out loud and enjoy brainstorming in groups.
Introverts: May prefer one-on-one interactions or small groups.
Extroverts: May prefer large gatherings and social events.
